This Knee Osteoarthritis Dataset offers a rich, clinically relevant resource for understanding the progression, diagnosis, and management of OA. Its combination of radiographic detail, clinical scoring, patient history, and lifestyle data makes it especially powerful for building predictive models, performing statistical analyses, or training AI systems for medical imaging.

By providing this level of detail across 1,000 patients, it enables robust and meaningful insights into one of the most common degenerative joint diseases affecting the aging population.
